Chile’s second chance at the nitrogen market
                    Marcelo Mena-Carrasco 
            ORCID: orcid.org/0000-0002-8847-75881,2

Nature Reviews Clean Technology

(2026) Cite this article

Subjects

            Climate-change mitigationEnvironmental impact

A century after Haber–Bosch ended Chile’s reign as a nitrogen supplier to the world, its green hydrogen and ammonia production could power fertilizer manufacturing and maritime shipping globally. Marcelo Mena-Carrasco argues that permitting and long-term industrial policy are needed to embrace this opportunity.

